The paper deals with the problem of super-resolving the appearance of 3D objects using deep learning techniques. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of normal maps, which are commonly used in computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of deep learning methods also suggests the possibility of using techniques such as convolutional neural networks (cs.LG) and generative adversarial networks (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the creation of a new dataset, which could also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
